          <div class="cons"><div class="pc-title">Watch out for</div><div class="pc-item">Gets expensive as list grows</div><div class="pc-item">Less powerful than Klaviyo for ecommerce</div><div class="pc-item">Automation builder less flexible than ActiveCampaign</div><div class="pc-item">Some advanced features locked to higher plans</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card"><div class="card-title">Frequently Asked Questions</div><div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Is Mailchimp free? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button><div class="faq-a">Mailchimp's free plan supports up to 500 contacts and 1,000 email sends per month — enough for most small businesses getting started. The free plan includes templates, basic automations, a landing page builder and audience analytics. Paid plans start at $13/month for up to 500 contacts with more sends and advanced features.</div></div><div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Is Mailchimp good for ecommerce? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button><div class="faq-a">Mailchimp works for ecommerce but Klaviyo is significantly better if you're running a Shopify store. Mailchimp's ecommerce integrations and automation depth don't match Klaviyo's, and its revenue attribution is less accurate. For non-ecommerce businesses — service businesses, creators, nonprofits — Mailchimp is excellent.</div></div><div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Mailchimp vs Klaviyo — which should I choose? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button><div class="faq-a">Choose Klaviyo if you run an ecommerce store — it's built specifically for online retail with deeper Shopify integration and more powerful abandoned cart and post-purchase flows. Choose Mailchimp if you're a service business, creator, nonprofit or any brand not primarily selling physical products online. Mailchimp is easier to use and has a better free plan.</div></div></div>
